commit.message: Try to fix unicode normalisation test in Windows.
Rewrite the test code generation for the unicode normalisation test, making sure that we always write UTF-8 source files.
Try to fix failures to print the compilation status for modules with non-ascii names (on Windows).
Set I/O encoding to UTF-8 on appveyor to fix output problems.
Fix printing of non-ascii module paths in cythonize() for Py2.
Help with remote debugging environment encoding problems in test runs.
Explicitly set I/O encoding in travis to make the test runner workers inherit it (instead of defaulting to ASCII in Py2).
Fix printing of non-ascii module paths in cythonize() for Py2.
Revert: Explicitly set I/O encoding in travis to make the test runner workers inherit it (instead of defaulting to ASCII in Py2).
Explicitly set I/O encoding for subprocesses in parallel cythonize() runs to make the test runner workers inherit it (instead of defaulting to ASCII in Py2).
Use a Latin-1 Unicode character in the test for Unicode module names to make it more compatible with Windows file system character sets (such as CP-1252).
Properly decode source and module file name from the FS encoding in Py2. Previously, with ASCII module names, UTF-8 decoding always worked, but wasn't correct.
Remove I/O encoding setting again (hope it's not needed any more).
Fall back to default encoding for test runner output if "sys.stdout.encoding" is not set.
